<br>
How is that, because a bunch of countries do not support your country policy that you would boycot its products?<br>
Of course we need you, and we know it since a long time, the only problem is that you need us exactly the same way, which you seem to have trouble understanding.<br>
<br>
Oh, before i  get flammed for this, with &quot;us&quot; i mean the rest of the world, France included.<br>
You are certainly aware of what will happen the day Japan and China take back their investments into USA to put it somewhere else, arent you.<br>
<br>
But, back to the subject.<br>
<br>
Ill stick to my opinion, sorry, the only country isolated atm is USA, and thats your administration's fault.<br>
Ask Redorious if M.Blair isnt feeling a bit alone atm and wondering about his future atm...just like M.Aznar and Berlusconi probably.<br>
<br>
France isnt agaisnt USA, but we are for UN and international right, international democracy is an important concept out here.<br>
<br>
So as your country is sitting on UN day after day a little more, it will be more and more difficult for France to defend both its friendship with USA and its trust in UN, thats as simple as that.<br>
<br>
Of course you are going to claim that USA are working with UN...and thats right, but before France intervention, it was more about the UN to acknowledge everything M.Powel would ask, and nothing more.<br>
<br>
Now, USA have to really work with UN, and not pretend they do, like they intended at the beginning, and thats what makes enrage M.Rumfeld and co, and why they want to make us pay, of course France would be the first, for this unforgivable act of rebelion.<br>
<br>
The problem is, here we dont see that as an act of rebelion, we see UN, international right, and the common desire to disarm Irak in peace, in order to prevent a slaughtering at Europeans doors.<br>
<br>
We dont have any anti-US campaign in our media, no insults and hatred, no racism.<br>
Can you honestly say the same?<br>
<br>
75 per cent people in Europe are against a war in the present situation, it happens that Chirac is speaking for them, along with Schroeder.<br>
<br>
And what about those 10 millions people in the streets last Saturday, to protest against the concept of preventive war?<br>
Were those people also &quot;neo-Marxists&quot;? =)<br>
<br>
<br>
-Belarkan<br>
