<br>
Germany suffered a long, on going humiliation, and that's what caused part of the problem. Also it was hard for many to understand or accept *how* they had been defeated. &quot;It was the Jews! the Socialists! the Wealthy! The Poor! The Ups! The Downs!...&quot;<br>
  It's part of human nature that if you get into a &quot;fair fight&quot;, the other guy beats you fairer, it's easier to accept usually, and that also applies to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>national psyches</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. That means the long term consequences are easier to deal with...sounds trite but it's true, that's one reason why wars are now fought as quickly and cleanly as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>possible</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
  If you are beaten swiftly and hard, it's humbling, but if you're kicked when your down, backstabbed, betrayed etc that's humiliating and humiliation leads to long lasting hate.  Even international politics is largely based on simple human emotions, you don't head that you get stomped, you play it well you're a hero. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caenn>Caenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 2:53:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=128>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> And now that I've simmered down a tad...<br>
